Cisco Packet Tracer Labs
🎯 Objective

Learn how to build, configure, and troubleshoot networks using Cisco Packet Tracer while applying the networking concepts you've already studied.

What is Cisco Packet Tracer?

Cisco Packet Tracer is a network simulation software developed by Cisco.

It allows you to:

Build virtual networks
Configure routers and switches
Practice networking commands
Test routing and switching
Simulate real-world network environments
Why Use Packet Tracer?

Instead of only reading networking concepts, Packet Tracer lets you:

Configure IP addresses
Create VLANs
Configure routers
Test connectivity
Observe packet flow
Troubleshoot network issues
